{\*\generator Msftedit 5.41.15.1515;}\viewkind4\uc1\pard\sa195\cf1\b\f0\fs20 This data view reads and writes the XML file directly. Even though the XML elements are mixed with text, you can read and update them directly using the XML View.\par
For the text between the XML data, the \cf2 DbXmlMixedGet()\cf1  function can be used. The format is:\par
\cf2 DbXmlMixedGet\cf1 (\b0\i\f1 Source\b\i0\f0 , \b0\i\f1 Path\b\i0\f0 , \b0\i\f1 Element\b\i0\f0 ) where:\par
\b0\i\f1 Source\b\i0\f0 =The data source to be used. This must be opened in the task, either as a Main source, linked source, or Declare.\par
\b0\i\f1 Path\b\i0\f0 =The XML path to this element, including the occurance number if there is more than one.\par
\b0\i\f1 Element\b\i0\f0 =The text after this element will be fetched.\par
}
